title: Softball: Branch takes No. 3 seed from Region 8-
text:
By AccessWDUN Staff Related Articles Softball: North Hall clinches 8-AAAA title game berth Softball: Buford takes out North Oconee to move into 8-AAAA title bout Softball: Region tournaments finally back in action after rainouts Softball: Lady Trojans take opening series of 8-AAAA tournament 
The Flowery Branch softball team defeated Winder-Barrow 5-2 on Thursday to secure the No. 3 seed from Region 8- . 
The Lady Falcons will travel to take on Alexander on Wednesday in the first round of the state playoffs. 
Bailey Sims led the way for the Branch, as she went 2 for 3. Courtney Harris, Cally Alexzulian and Maddie Hetzel also supplied key hits to help secure the victory. 
Freshman pitcher Alyssa Kimbrell went 5 innings in the start, while sophomore Kara Kight came on in relief to notch the win. Associated Tags : High school softball, Flowery Branch softball Â© Copyright 2015 AccessWDUN.com
